headline: UnitedHealthcare and other insurers are pulling info about execs offline after a CEO was killed
summary: UnitedHealthcare (UNH) has taken down its leadership page from its website, following the fatal shooting of its CEO Brian Thompson on Wednesday. The move was mirrored by several other major health insurers, including Anthem Blue Cross Blue Shield and Elevance Health (ELV).
